The missing COVID-19 patient from Osun State Isolation Centre in Ejigbo has been apprehended and returned to the centre, The PUNCH reports. The patient, a woman, was apprehended in Ejigbo town and returned to the facility by the police on Saturday afternoon. Chief Press Secretary to Osun State Governor, Ismail Omipidan, confirmed the development to The PUNCH. He said that the patient had been apprehended and returned to the facility. Details later… Reports in various quarters indicate that six persons with coronavirus have escaped from isolation centre in Ejigbo, Osun State. Already, a special manhurt has been reportedly established by the state government in a bid to re-capture the fleeing patients. The six escaped persons, according to a signed statement, belong to a… April 4, 2020 In "News" OSOGBO - Following the panic induced by the story trending in the social media that six suspected coronavirus patients have escaped from the Ejigbo Isolation Centre, the Osun State Government has said that only one person is missing from the centre.The State Commissioner for Information and Civic Orientation, Mrs Funke… April 4, 2020 In "News" By Olajide Idowu Osogbo - The Osun government on Wednesday appealed to the Federal Government to come to its aid in containing the spread of COVID-19 in the state as confirmed cases rose to 14 from the initial two. Mr Ismail Omipidan, the Chief Press Secretary to Gov. Gboyega Oyetola,… April 1, 2020 In "News"